        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Screaming Terror has two components.  The mez and the memory wipe component.  If its resisted both fail.  If its successful, then the initial mez may work, but the memory wipe does not.  If you were standing closer to the gobby when ST wore off, he would come after you immediately.  Just that you are out of the extremely low aggro range of the gob the way you are doing it.</P><P> You can easily counter this by FDing after a successful cast of ST.  Maybe do it after you kill the first, and just before you pulll the second.  This will erase your aggro, as long as the mob is on its spawn point.</P><P> Honestly I didnt have any trouble pulling these guys.  You can easily take two of them by just tossing dark and fear on both while they beat on pet and fear em.  Ping pong one until the other is dead, then make sure to grab one the instant it pops next round.</P><P> Good luck and happy gobby bashin.</P><P><b><font color=blue>Retrievil Hesevil</font id=blue></b><BR><font color=red><b>58 DE Necromancer - Tallon Zek</font id=red></b><BR><font color=blue><b>55 Iksar Necromancer - Rodcet Nife</b></font id=blue><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=333155" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=333155</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
