        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         ST works as follows:</P><P>If it is not resisted, the mob gets mezzed for 18 seconds or till it takes damage (from someone attacking it or from a dot tick going off).  It also has the ability to stun, meaning it will interupt casting of mobs if it is not resisted.  </P><P>The mem blur componant only works at random.  I beleive mobs that are lvs 35 and lower will have a much greater chance of forgeting you.  Mobs above that lv will still have a chance to forget you, but it could be lower.  Hope that helps.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=191272" target="_blank">Merkurion Everdeth</a><BR>=--60 Warlock of The Rathe--=<BR>Member of <a href="http://66.205.128.39/" target="_blank">Tindi' Losi</a></P><P>"Get busy living, or get busy dying" -The Shawshank Redemption<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
