         And one more thing about the memblur side of the equation: NEVER COUNT ON IT.</P><P>Using Dazzle and Reoccurring Amnesia with my enchanter, if I sat on mezz break or MA didn't give a Taunt or two, I always took a post mezz smack or two, especially if I had Tashed or Slowed. If enchanter mezz with a 20% memblur component followed by a 3-cast memblur failed most times, I am pretty sure the memblur of ST is a trivial thing at best and relies heavily on FD.</P><P>Verant has always excelled at reducing the frequency that any useful spell ever actually works. Memblur is a wonderful tool that seldomly works as intended.</P><P><b>Venjenz</b></P><P>"...the darkest magic...my soul swims in it."<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
